    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Debate Over Honoring Poland's Jews; A Revealing Dispute</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sandi Merle letter, commenting on Dec 20 article, deplores cries by Polish extremists at Auschwitz that Polish Jews should get off Polish soil; says they show why Jews must support Israel</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Poles and Jews Feud About Crosses at Auschwitz'' (news article, Dec. 20):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Poles and Jews Feud About Crosses at Auschwitz'' (news article, Dec. 20):</p>
        <p>I have no doubt that through prudent dialogue the issue of crosses outside the Auschwitz death camp will eventually be resolved.</p>
        <p>However, I am saddened that this dispute reveals that the more things change, the more they stay the same.</p>
        <p>Even Jews detained at Auschwitz would acknowledge that Jews were not the only ones who suffered and died there. But anyone wondering why Jews of the disapora are so supportive of Israel should take note of the cries by Polish extremists that Polish Jews should get off Polish soil.</p>
        <p>SANDI MERLE  New York, Dec. 21, 1998</p>
      </block>
